title: Incredibly Strange Music, Volume II
description: "Incredibly Strange Music" is a comprehensive guide to little-known yet amazing vinyl recordings -- mostly from the 50s, 60s, and 70s -- like Muhammad Ali Fights Tooth Decay, Jayne Mansfield reading Shakespeare, Tchaikovsky and Me, Sebastion Cabot (yes, Mr. French of Family Affair) "singing" songs by Bob Dylan, and tons more
author: A. Juno
